A Senator representing Gombe North Senatorial District in the National Assembly, Saidu Ahmed Alkali, has donated the sum of N6 million to the victims of flood disaster in Dukku Local Government Area of Gombe State. The senator announced the donation when he visited Dukku, Hashidu, Jamari, Lafiya Tale, Malala and Wuro Tale affected by a devastating flood that washed away farmlands, houses and claimed lives. Senator Alkali donated N1 million to each of the six affected communities. Speaking at the palace of Emir of Dukku, the lawmaker said he was there to commiserate with the emirate and the entire people of the LGA over the flood disaster. Alkali added that he visited the affected communities with the officials of the National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) to assess the level of destruction for prompt intervention. He prayed for the repose of the souls of those that lost their lives and commiserated with those who lostÂ  their properties. In his response, the Emir of Dukku, Alhaji Haruna Abdulkadir Rashid II, thanked the senator adding that the gesture was a demonstration of his love and care to the electorate.  NEMA distributes sewing machines, water pumps to flood victims NEMA donates relief materials to Gombe flood, blast victims Agony, pains of Kogi flood victims OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY